    slug: "minhaj-ul-muslim-urdu",
    description: `Minhaj ul Muslim is a comprehensive and widely respected Urdu-language Islamic reference book authored by the distinguished scholar Shaykh Abu Bakr Jabir Al-Jazairi, originally written in Arabic under the title "Minhaj al-Muslim" and translated into Urdu to serve the vast Urdu-speaking Muslim population. This monumental work serves as a complete guide to Islamic belief, worship, character, and daily conduct, covering virtually every aspect of a Muslim's religious life in a single, well-organised volume. The book is structured into four major sections that correspond to the foundational pillars of Islamic knowledge and practice. The first section deals with Aqidah (Islamic creed and belief), providing a detailed and scholarly exposition of the six articles of faith: belief in Allah, His angels, His revealed books, His messengers, the Day of Judgement, and divine predestination. The author presents the correct Islamic beliefs based on the Quran and the authentic Sunnah, carefully addressing common misconceptions and deviations that have appeared throughout Islamic history. The second section covers Ibadah (acts of worship), providing comprehensive guidance on the five daily prayers, fasting in Ramadan, Zakat, and Hajj, along with detailed explanations of the supplications, remembrances, and etiquettes associated with each act of worship. Each chapter in this section includes the relevant Quranic verses and hadith narrations that serve as the evidential basis for the rulings presented. The third section addresses Muamalat (social dealings and transactions), covering topics such as marriage and family life, business transactions, inheritance, food and drink regulations, and interactions with others in society. The fourth and final section focuses on Akhlaq (Islamic character and morals), presenting the ethical and behavioural standards that every Muslim should strive to embody, drawn directly from the example of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) and his noble companions. The Urdu translation preserves the scholarly depth and clarity of the original Arabic while making the content accessible to readers who may not be proficient in Arabic. This imported edition is printed on quality paper with clear typography that makes extended reading comfortable. Minhaj ul Muslim has earned its reputation as one of the most reliable and comprehensive Islamic references available, and this Urdu edition ensures that the wealth of knowledge it contains is accessible to students, scholars, and ordinary Muslims throughout the Urdu-speaking world who seek a trustworthy guide to living their faith in accordance with the authentic teachings of Islam.`,
