    slug: "miracles-and-merits-of-allahs-messenger",
    description: `Miracles and Merits of Allah's Messenger is an English-language book that presents a detailed and well-documented collection of the miracles (mu'jizat) performed by Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) along with an examination of his unique merits and virtues that distinguish him from all other human beings in Islamic theology. This book systematically compiles the authenticated accounts of the prophetic miracles from the major hadith collections and classical Islamic sources, organising them into categories that help the reader appreciate the breadth and significance of the miraculous evidence supporting the prophethood of Muhammad (peace be upon him). The book covers the major categories of miracles, beginning with the Quran itself, which is universally recognised in Islam as the greatest and most enduring miracle of the Prophet, a literary and spiritual masterpiece that no human being has been able to replicate despite the challenge it poses. The narrative then moves to the physical miracles, including the splitting of the moon, the miraculous journey of Isra and Mi'raj, the flowing of water from the Prophet's fingers, the increase of food through his blessing, the healing of the sick through his supplication, the speaking of inanimate objects testifying to his prophethood, and numerous other well-authenticated miracles that were witnessed by his companions and recorded in the hadith literature. Each miracle is presented with its chain of narration and an assessment of its authenticity, allowing readers to distinguish between well-established accounts and those that are less reliably transmitted. The second major section of the book is devoted to the merits and virtues of the Prophet (peace be upon him), drawing upon the extensive body of hadith narrations that describe his noble character, his physical appearance, his knowledge, his generosity, his courage, his humility, his compassion, and the many qualities that made him the most excellent of all human beings. The author also addresses the prophecies contained in earlier scriptures that foretold the coming of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him), the universal nature of his message, and the transformative impact that his teachings had on the Arabian Peninsula and subsequently on the entire world. The book is written in clear, scholarly English that makes this important subject accessible to readers who may not have access to the original Arabic sources. It serves as a valuable reference for da'wah purposes, for students of Islamic studies, and for any Muslim who wishes to deepen their knowledge and appreciation of the miraculous evidence that supports the prophethood of Muhammad (peace be upon him) and the extraordinary qualities that made him the chosen messenger of Allah for all of humanity until the end of time.`,
