    slug: "miracles-of-the-messenger-pbuh",
    description: `Miracles of the Messenger (PBUH) is a focused English-language work that examines the supernatural events and miraculous signs associated with Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) as recorded in the authentic Islamic sources. This book is dedicated exclusively to the topic of miracles (mu'jizat), providing a thorough and scholarly treatment of one of the most important aspects of Islamic belief regarding the finality and truth of the Prophet's mission. The author presents each miracle within its proper historical and evidential context, explaining not only what occurred but also the significance of each event in terms of its role as a divine sign confirming the authenticity of the Prophet's claim to receiving revelation from Allah. The book begins with a foundational chapter explaining the Islamic concept of miracles, how they differ from magic, sorcery, and extraordinary natural events, and the criteria that Islamic scholarship uses to evaluate reports of miraculous events. This methodological introduction equips readers with the analytical tools needed to understand the material that follows. The miracles are then presented in a systematic order, starting with the miracle of the Quran, which the book treats at length given its position as the most comprehensive and lasting of all prophetic miracles, noting how its linguistic inimitability, its consistency over twenty-three years of revelation, its scientific accuracy, its prophecies, and its preservation from alteration all serve as evidence of its divine origin. The book then covers the major physical miracles, including the splitting of the moon, the night journey to Jerusalem and the ascension to the heavens, the tree trunk that cried when the Prophet stopped using it as a minbar, the stones that greeted the Prophet with salam, the food that increased through his blessing to feed large gatherings, and the various instances of healing and protection that occurred through his supplication. Each account is accompanied by references to the relevant hadith sources and an assessment of the strength of the narration, allowing readers to understand the evidential basis for each miracle. The book also addresses the common objections and questions that critics raise regarding prophetic miracles, providing thoughtful and well-reasoned responses based on Islamic scholarship and rational argumentation. The writing style is clear, engaging, and accessible to English-speaking readers, making this book suitable for both general readers who are curious about the miraculous aspects of the Prophet's life and students of Islamic studies who require a reliable reference on this topic. This work serves as a powerful reminder of the divine support that accompanied the Prophet throughout his mission and strengthens the reader's faith in the truth of his message.`,
