    slug: "mishkat-al-masabih-3-vols-set-amm",
    description: `Mishkat Al-Masabih is a renowned and comprehensive three-volume collection of hadith (sayings and actions of Prophet Muhammad, peace be upon him) compiled by the eminent scholar Shaykh Al-Khatib Al-Tabrizi, who organised this monumental work as an expanded and improved version of the earlier collection known as Masabih al-Sunnah by Imam Al-Baghawi. This particular edition is published by Darussalam and carries the AMM (Al-Maktabah Al-Madaniyyah) designation, indicating it is the approved edition that has been reviewed for accuracy, quality of translation, and adherence to scholarly standards. The three-volume set covers virtually every aspect of Islamic life and practice through the authentic hadith narrations, making it one of the most comprehensive hadith references available in Urdu translation. The collection is organised thematically into chapters and sections that correspond to the major topics of Islamic jurisprudence, theology, ethics, and social conduct. The opening chapters cover matters of faith (iman), including belief in Allah, the angels, the revealed books, the messengers, the Day of Judgement, and divine predestination. Subsequent chapters cover the five pillars of Islam in extensive detail, with the chapters on prayer (Salah) being particularly comprehensive, covering everything from the conditions and prerequisites of prayer to the detailed description of the Prophet's prayer, the recommended supplications, and the common errors that people make. The volumes also include extensive coverage of fasting, Zakat, Hajj, marriage and divorce, business transactions, food and drink regulations, clothing and adornment, etiquettes of sleeping and waking, sickness and death, funerals, the description of Paradise and Hell, the virtues of various actions and times, and the warnings against sins and innovations. Each hadith is presented with its full chain of narrators and a grading that indicates its level of authenticity, drawing upon the work of the great hadith scholars such as Imam Al-Bukhari, Imam Muslim, Imam Al-Tirmidhi, Imam Abu Dawud, Imam Al-Nasai, and Imam Ibn Majah. The Urdu translation is clear, accurate, and faithful to the meaning of the original Arabic, making this collection accessible to the vast Urdu-speaking Muslim community. The three volumes are bound in durable hard covers with quality paper and clear printing that ensures comfortable reading even during extended study sessions. This set is an indispensable reference for scholars, students of Islamic knowledge, imams, and serious lay readers who wish to have access to a comprehensive and reliable collection of the prophetic traditions that form the second source of Islamic law after the Quran.`,
