    slug: "missing-out-on-rewards",
    description: `Missing Out on Rewards is a concise yet impactful English-language Islamic book that addresses the common problem of Muslims losing out on the abundant rewards and blessings that Allah has made available through seemingly simple acts of worship and devotion. The book highlights how many Muslims unknowingly deprive themselves of tremendous spiritual benefits by neglecting or being unaware of the many opportunities for earning reward that exist in everyday life. The author draws upon the authentic hadith narrations of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) to identify specific actions, phrases, and habits that carry extraordinary rewards yet are often overlooked or undervalued by Muslims. The book covers a wide range of topics, beginning with the rewards associated with the daily prayers, including the additional prayers (Sunnah and Nawafil) that many people neglect despite their immense spiritual benefits, the importance of praying in congregation at the mosque, the rewards of the first row in prayer, and the multiplied rewards of prayer during specific times and in specific locations such as the Haramain. The book then addresses the rewards of dhikr (remembrance of Allah), explaining how simple phrases such as SubhanAllah, Alhamdulillah, Allahu Akbar, La ilaha illallah, and various other forms of remembrance carry rewards that most people fail to appreciate, including the filling of the scales on the Day of Judgement, the forgiveness of sins, the planting of trees in Paradise, and the elevation of one's spiritual rank. The author also discusses the rewards associated with acts of kindness, charity, maintaining family ties, honouring parents, visiting the sick, comforting the grieving, feeding others, and various other forms of good conduct that carry far greater rewards than most people realise. The book highlights specific opportunities that are time-sensitive, such as the rewards available during the blessed days and nights of Ramadan, the first ten days of Dhul Hijjah, Fridays, the hours before Fajr, and other special times when rewards are multiplied manifold. The author emphasises that one of the greatest tragedies of the Muslim community is the accumulation of missed opportunities for reward that can never be recovered once they have passed, urging readers to be more conscious and intentional about seizing every available opportunity to earn Allah's pleasure. The writing style is direct and motivational, designed to inspire readers to take immediate action rather than merely reading and setting the book aside. This short but powerful book is an excellent read for anyone who wishes to maximise their spiritual earnings and ensure that they are not among those who will regret their negligence on the Day when every missed opportunity will become painfully apparent.`,
    metaDescription: "Missing Out on Rewards highlights overlooked opportunities for spiritual blessings in daily worship, dhikr, and good deeds based on authentic hadith."
